Craft and Capture Packets Using Scapy
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Install and configure Scapy for packet manipulation
Craft custom network packets with various protocols
Capture and filter network traffic in real-time
Analyze packet structures and protocol behaviors
Automate packet operations using Python scripts
Prerequisites
Students should have:

Basic Python programming knowledge
Understanding of TCP/IP networking concepts
Familiarity with Linux command line
Knowledge of common network protocols (TCP, UDP, ICMP)
Lab Environment
Al Nafi provides pre-configured Linux cloud machines. Click Start Lab to access your environment with:

Ubuntu Linux with Python 3
Scapy and dependencies pre-installed
Network tools and utilities
Root/sudo access for packet operations
Task 1: Install and Verify Scapy
Step 1.1: Update System and Install Scapy
sudo apt update
sudo apt install python3-pip python3-dev libpcap-dev -y
sudo pip3 install scapy
Step 1.2: Verify Installation
sudo python3 -c "from scapy.all import *; print('Scapy version:', scapy.__version__)"
Step 1.3: Identify Network Interface
ip addr show
Note your primary interface name (typically eth0 or ens3).

